post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

Today, we were notified that we have several student athletes and other members of our student body who attended a party over the weekend and are now exhibiting symptoms that could be related to COVID-19. Those symptoms include fever, loss of taste and smell, diarrhea and vomiting. Those student’s parents have been notified and those students have been sent home.

As a result, we are cancelling this week's JV football game against Woodville on Thursday, the Varsity Football game against Woodville Friday and the volleyball game against Warren.on Friday.

We have disinfected the campus today. Diboll has strict protocols in place to prevent the spread of COVID-19 and our students and staff do a tremendous job while they are on campus following those protocols. Parents, we ask your assistance in stressing the importance of masking up, social distancing and hand washing while they are away from school to help us be able to continue our extracurricular activities and to keep students in school.

Thanks,
Vicki Thomas
Diboll ISD
Superintendent

post_text:
Tonight the Diboll Lumberjacks will play a scrimmage against the Corrigan Bulldogs. There are no tickets being sold for this game but there is a maximum of 50% stadium capacity allowed and we will be counting each person as they enter and when the 50% capacity is reached, no one else will be allowed to enter. There is also no re-entry if you leave the stadium for any reason. The following guidelines will be followed and enforced.
1. Masks or Face Coverings will be properly worn by all attendees.
2. Social distancing guidelines of 6 feet between all family groups.
3. No spectators will be allowed on the field at anytime before, during or after the games.

Thank you for you cooperation and know that these guidelines are for your safety and the safety of our students and staff to ensure that we will be able to continue participating in extracurricular activities.

post_text:
Free curbside meal pick-up will be available for Asynchronous and Synchronous at-home learners. Pick-up times will be from 4:30 pm - 6:30 pm at the back of H.G. Temple campus. The first meal pick-up date will be Wednesday, August 19th and normal meal pick-up dates will begin Monday, August 24th and continue every Monday and Thursday.

Meal Pick-up Process
Parents/guardians can pick up meals with the following proof of enrollment, children do not need to be present to pick up meals:
Student ID Number (lunch number)
Report Card
Official letter from the campus
Once parents provide proof of enrollment, they will receive the student's ID card for easy continued meal pick-up.

Curbside meals can only be provided to enrolled Diboll ISD students attending at-home learning.

Meals on Monday pick-up will contain breakfast and lunch for Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday. Meals for pick-up on Thursday will contain breakfast and lunch for Friday and Monday. Menu and cooking instructions will be provided in each meal pack.

The high school will provide assistance with Online Registration. If you do not have a computer or internet access, we will be set up at Walter Allen Park from 4-6 p.m., Monday August 10, 2020. The park is located across from the Diboll Housing Authority. 702 South First Street.

The following CDC protocols will need to be in place for your safety:
1. Masks (if you do not have one, we will provide it for you)
2. Hand Sanitizer must be used prior to using a keyboard.
3. High School staff will sanitize after each use.
4. Stations will be six feet apart.

Remember if you do not choose your method of learning today, August 10, we must assume that you plan on face-to-face campus instruction for the 2020-2021.

post_text: The following Diboll High School FFA members have been awarded their Lonestar Degree; Noah Farr, Gracie Crager and Sidney Hyland. This is the highest degree of membership the State FFA Association can award. FFA members may apply to receive the Lone Star Degree only after they have received the Chapter degree. Those wishing to receive their Lone Star Degree must have been an active FFA member for at least two years, complete at least four semesters of agricultural science at or above the ninth grade level, maintain a supervised agricultural experience (SAE) program, invest significant time and money in their SAE, demonstrate their leadership skills and show a commitment to the FFA through involvement at the chapter level and above. This degree of active membership is usually awarded at the state level during the Texas FFA convention which unfortunately was not held this year. Join us in congratulating these three on this huge accomplishment.

post_text: Diboll ISD would like to do a social media project called “Senior stories” where students or staff can send in a 30 second video of themselves reflecting on their time at Diboll High School or thanking individuals who helped them on their journey to graduation or staff sending encouragement to their graduating Seniors. The plan is that we will put the clips together in an end of the year video to post for all to see via YouTube. I know not all may want to do this but we would like to give you all the opportunity to say some final thoughts to your classmates, teachers or students since your time on the campus of DHS was cut short. Please share your videos with us via Google Drive at callen@dibollisd.org. We are so proud of our Seniors and know they have missed a lot of last events this semester but we thought this video project might help give our Seniors a chance to share some final thoughts about their time in Diboll ISD. So start making and sending in those videos. Deadline to submit videos will be Sunday, May 17 at 11:59 pm.

IMPORTANT UPDATE! In order to limit contact and for the safety of our staff, parents and students, there will be a change to the meal service days. Pick up days will change to Monday and Thursday. Expect to receive meals for 3 days on Mondays and 2 days of meals on Thursdays. Menus, cooking and food safety instructions will be provided with each meal pack. We hope this will assist families by reducing the number of trips needed to pick up meals for their children.
We will follow the same time schedule as before. Due to the increase in food items being delivered, please allow for additional time our drivers may need to make it to each stop. All location and time information is included on the posted menu. **Menus are subject to change due to product availability.

**AMENDMENT: In light of the COVID19 virus, the administration building will be closed to the public. However, the public can observe the monthly board meeting live through the DISD Facebook page at www.facebook.com/dibolljacks . Those wishing to participate in public comment must submit their remarks via email to callen@dibollisd.org no later than 6:30 PM today. The remarks will be read aloud by the Board President during the public comment portion of the meeting.

This Amendment is being made in response to the Order effective today, March 30, 2020 at 11:59 AM by the Angelina County Office of Emergency Management and pertains solely to the manner in which the meeting will take place and not with regard to any subject matter on the Agenda. This action is being taken in good faith, consistent with Section 551.0411 of the Texas Open Meetings Act, and not intended to circumvent the Act.**

Through this crisis, our primary concern is the health and safety of voters, election workers, and our local election officials. Therefore, on March 20, 2020 at an Emergency Meeting of the Board of Trustees it was unanimously approved to postpone the May 2, 2020 Election to the November 3, 2020 uniform election.

post_text:
To ensure continuation of educational services, we will be distributing instructional packets and technology devices as needed by grade level.

This Friday, March 20th, from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m., campuses will be distributing the first series of these instructional packets by grade level and course that are required to be completed by all students. We ask that parents drive up/ walk up to each campus their child / children attend and receive the instructional materials. For high school students, they may pick up their instructional materials in the high school cafeteria this Friday from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. as well. related.

As per best health practices, we will allow 10 high school students into the cafeteria at one time to quickly receive their packets and then depart the campus. We also ask that you visit the campus websites where your student(s) attend for more specific details regarding completion of online work and off-line work, due dates, when the next learning packets will need to be picked up,etc.

Thank you again for being a partner in your child’s education.

Diboll ISD is excited to announce another free internet promotion. Altice USA (Sudenlink) is committed to helping schools and students stay connected during this unprecedented time. For households with K-12 and/or college students who may be displaced due to school closures and who do not currently have home internet access, we are offering our Altice Advantage 30 Mbps broadband solution for free for 60 days to any new customer household within our footprint.

Eligible households interested in this solution can use the following to fill out an application.

Online: alticeadvantageinternet.com
Click the "See if you qualify" link at the bottom of the page.

Call 1-844-358-3147

Families can qualify for participating in the National Free Lunch Program. A letter of participation is required as proof; Diboll ISD has posted a letter on our home page, www.dibollisd.com. Letter can be downloaded/printed by clicking the “Diboll ISD Community Eligibility Provision” link on our home page.

In Diboll ISD, the health, safety, and well-being of our students and staff are our top priorities. It is a tremendous responsibility and one that we take very seriously. We are monitoring the updates and following guidance from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and Angelina County Health District.

In an effort to support a safe learning and teaching environment for students and staff, we are asking all members of the DISD community to complete a brief travel survey before returning to school on Monday, March 16. For those who indicate they or a member of their household have traveled out of the country or attended a large gathering event (concerts, theme parks, etc..), we ask that you monitor for possible signs and symptoms for 14-days since returning home.

We thank you for your continued partnership as we collectively focus on the health of our students, staff, families, and community.

Survey is available at the following link.

Attention Parents -

Tomorrow our Diboll Lumberjack Basketball Team will be playing in the Regional Finals at Midway High School at 7:30 p.m. in Waco, TX. We have an enormous fan base of parents, students and staff who want to show their support for Coach Davis, Coach Rios, and our outstanding young men. Waco is a 3 1/2 hour drive and we want everyone to be able to take their time and drive safely. As a result, we will be dismissing all students and staff at 1:00 p.m. tomorrow, Friday, March 6th. For our Pre - K 3 Students, their schedule for tomorrow will be as follows: Morning Classes - 7:45 a.m. - 10:45 a.m. and afternoon classes - 10:45 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. Please come out and support this amazing group of young men and coaches and have a wonderful start to Spring Break.

FFA makes a positive difference in the lives of students by developing their potential for premier leadership, personal growth and career success through agricultural education. FFA membership today is comprised of 700,170 student members in grades seven through 12 who belong to one of 8,612 local FFA chapters throughout the United States, Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. FFA operates on local, state and national levels.

Get involved with your local FFA Chapter.

post_text:
Ladyjack Volleyball is rolling strong, having completed the non-district portion of the season last friday. The Lady Jacks are ranked #11 in the STATE in Class 3A, and own a 25-7 record.

Last night, the Lady Eagles from Woodville, who have aspirations for a district championship, dared venture to the Woodshed, and left in shambles, as your Lady Jacks dismantled them from the start. Helene Bolton and Kylie Rios could do ANYTHING they wanted on offense, and Cristbel Ramos, Maddi Horton, and others made it extremely difficult for the ball to hit the ground.

"Coach Stewart feels his team took care of business last night, and each person played up to what they are capable of. He stated it was a tough opponent, and at times the Ladyjacks made it look easy. It was fun to watch!"

Outstanding performances:

Helene Bolton: 3 aces, 12 kills, 10 digs, 3 blocks
Kylie Rios: 4 aces, 11 kills, 8 digs, 1 block
Ari Compean: 2 aces, 5 kills, 26 assists, 13 digs
Zayda Perez: 3 aces, 4 kills, 10 assists, 3 digs, 2 blocks

The Lady Jacks improve to 26-7, 1-0 on the season.

post_text: Ladyjack Softball Area Playoff Information - Due to the inclement weather yesterday and today. Diboll will play Boling tomorrow, Saturday, May 4, 2019 at 3:00 p.m. at the Crosby High School Softball Sports Complex located at14670 FM 2100 Crosby, Tx 77532. The game will resume from the ending point of last night's game in New Caney. It will be the bottom of the second inning, score - Diboll - 2, Boling - 0. We will only play this one game, the winner will advance to the Regional Quarterfinals. Come out and Support your Ladyjack Softball team. Click map below for detailed directions to field.

post_text: We had 17 athletes participate in the area 7 track and field events today for Special Olympics at Abe Martin Stadium. Each athlete participated in 1 track and 1 field event which included 50m run, 100m run, 200m run, 100m wheelchair, Javelin throw, softball throw, and the long jump. We are very proud of our athletes!
